.TH "connection_broken" 9 "connection_broken" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
connection_broken \- Determine if the connection to the client is good
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" connection_broken
.BI "(struct scsi_info *vscsi "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vscsi" 12
Pointer to our adapter structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function attempts to send a ping MAD to the client. If the call to
queue the request returns H_CLOSED then the connection has been broken
and the function returns TRUE.

EXECUTION ENVIRONMENT:
Interrupt or Process environment
